### Accomplished

- **Profile overlay redesign**: removed `csq use` (no global mutable state). `~/.claude/settings.json` is canonical default; `settings-<name>.json` files are overlays containing only the diff. `csq run N -p mm` deep-merges overlay over default at startup, writes real file to `config-N/settings.json`. Stateless per run.
- **Single-account zero-friction**: `csq` (no args) auto-resolves: 0 accounts → exec vanilla `claude`; 1 account → use it; 2+ → ask which.
- **Unlimited accounts**: validation regex changed from `[1-7]` to `[1-9][0-9]*`.
- **Args pass-through**: `csq run N --resume` forwards all extra args to `claude`. Uses set-u-safe `${arr[@]+"${arr[@]}"}` pattern.
- **Targeted rotation**: `csq swap N` and `/rotate N` swap THIS terminal to a specific account in-place (no restart).
- **`⚡csq` statusline marker**: explicit prefix when CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR points at `~/.claude/accounts/config-N`.
- **Pre-symlinked all configs**: configs 1-6 had no `commands/` symlink (only config-7). Manually created 36 symlinks per config so `/rotate` works in every csq terminal.
- **Pre-converted settings.json to real files** in all 7 configs so existing terminals are isolated from `~/.claude/settings.json` mutations.
